  <description><![CDATA[<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;">Great for moderate and easy hikes</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">70km of hiking trails in the Portofino Natural Park</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">Incredible sea views</li>
<li style="text-align: left;">Lively bars, restaurants and shops to explore</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>The Ligurian towns near Portofino are an exciting mix of glamour and wealth with down to earth, rustic charm. Walking in the Portofino Natural Park reminds you that there's still a lot of rural land around these picture perfect towns. There are still farmers working on the land and old farm houses in the middle of the countryside. Walking here, is a great chance to get to know the real Liguria.</p>
<h4 style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Sea view walking</strong></h4>
<p>One of our favourite parts of walking in the Portofino area is looking down on the 'C' shaped harbours that are so characteristic of the area. The bright white yachts lining the harbour always look smart bobbing about on the water. From above, the multi-coloured buildings stand out against the lapis lazuli sea. See if you can spot any fisherman bringing in their catch. </p>
<h4 style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Fantastic public transport network</strong></h4>
<p>Trains run up and down the coast linking the resort with the city of Genoa and the beautiful <a data-udi="umb://document/79a94ac27eda4c2ea223bc0fe7fd99b6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/79a94ac27eda4c2ea223bc0fe7fd99b6}" title="Cinque Terre Area" data-anchor="#">Cinque Terre</a>, which is a bit further down the coast. From Rapallo it's easy to hop on the train to other nearby towns, all of which have gorgeous sea views and tucked away beaches.</p>
<h4 style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Buzzing caf</strong>é<strong>s and restaurants</strong></h4>
<p>There's a really communal feel in towns like Rapallo and Santa Margherita. Rapallo in particular is full of delicious restaurants and delis where you can sit on plastic chairs and grab a quick pasta salad for lunch. We love the down to earth restaurants, where you'll find Italian families eating together and enjoying themselves in the evenings. It really is buzzing!</p>
<h4 style="color: #00533a;"><strong>Central Hotels</strong></h4>
<p>Our hotels are all central making them an excellent base from which to explore this wonderful region. All you need to do is hop on a bus or a train and you'll find yourself in charming Portofino or the historical city of Genoa.</p>]]></description>
